Welcome To Triaxis Install Guide
This Guide Will Help You To Install Triaxis Correctly
Before You Install Flash Ubuntu Server Iso With Rufus Etcher Or Ventoy Make Sure That There Are No important Files Inside the USB Drive Then Backup Your Data On Your System Because It Will Erase Your Partition Drive After Installing Triaxis
1 enter https://ubuntu.com/download/server
2 Setup Ubuntu Server
3 Update Using sudo apt update
4 Install Kde Plasma Desktop sudo apt install kde-standard for base and servers dont install desktop environment if you Want Other Desktop Environment Go To https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Triaxis-GNU-Linux/blob/main/Other%20Desktop%20Environment
GRUB_TIMEOUT=0
Change them to:
GRUB_TIMEOUT_STYLE=menu
GRUB_TIMEOUT=5
update grub using sudo update-grub
5 Rename GRUB Menu Entries GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR=`lsb_release -i -s 2> /dev/null || echo Debian` Change it to: GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR="Triaxis GNU/Linux"
Then Update grub using sudo update-grub
6 Edit /etc/os-release sudo nano /etc/os-release Change NAME="Ubuntu"
PRETTY_NAME="Ubuntu 24.04 LTS"
To NAME="Triaxis"
PRETTY_NAME="Triaxis"
7 enable submenu sudo nano /etc/grub.d/10_linux then change GRUB_DISABLE_SUBMENU="true" to GRUB_DISABLE_SUBMENU="false" then sudo update-grub
8 Add A logo use figlet to install it use sudo apt install figlet then figlet TRI then press prt sc then click rectangular region then screenshot the TRI on figlet then name it to triaxis-logo.png then move the image to /usr/share/pixmaps/ sudo cp ~/your TRI Logo/triaxis-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/
Or You Can Download Triaxis Logo On Readme then theres a triaxis logo then Save Image As /home/yourname/Pictures then name it to Triaxis-logo.png then Open a terminal.
Use the mv command with sudo:
sudo mv /home/yourname/Picture/Triaxis-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/
the open sudo nano /etc/os-release then you find logo= then Cahnge to LOGO=/usr/share/pixmaps/Triaxis-logo.png

9 Replace The SDDM Use sudo apt install sddm-theme-lubuntu Locate Available SDDM Themes If you’re getting “Permission denied” when trying to change SDDM to use the LXQt theme, it usually means you don’t have the right privileges or the file isn’t writable by your user. Here’s how to fix it:
Run sudo nano /etc/sddm.conf If the file doesn’t exist, create it with root Generate a default config: sudo sddm --example-config > /etc/sddm.conf then edit it sudo nano /etc/sddm.conf Set LXQt theme in the config
Inside /etc/sddm.conf, add: [Theme]
Current=lubuntu
Restart SDDM Using sudo systemctl restart sddm
Themes are usually stored in: /usr/share/sddm/themes/
Edit the SDDM config file: with sudo nano /etc/sddm.conf If the file doesn’t exist, create it and add: [Theme]
Current=lubuntu
Or use the command sudo sddm --example-config > /etc/sddm.conf
Restart SDDM sudo systemctl restart sddm
Install Firefox with sudo apt update
sudo apt install firefox
10 Enable The Login And Logout Sound Open System Settings Then Personalization Then Notification Then Application-specific settings then configure then system services plasma workspace configure events then click Play a sound on login and logout sounds
11 Set ascii_distro="none" on nano ~/.config/neofetch/config.conf Because We Dont Need Neofetch Logo
12 Change the Link Open the os-release file sudo nano /etc/os-release
Find the line that looks like this: HOME_URL="https://www.ubuntu.com/"
Replace it to HOME_URL="https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Triaxis-GNU-Linux"
(Optional) You can also change other fields:
NAME="Triaxis GNU/Linux"
PRETTY_NAME="Triaxis GNU/Linux 1.0"
ID=triaxis
VERSION="1.0"
SUPPORT_URL="https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Triaxis-GNU-Linux/issues"
BUG_REPORT_URL="https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Triaxis-GNU-Linux/issues"
Save and exit (CTRL+O, CTRL+X in nano).
Restart Plasma session (log out and back in, or reboot).
Now, when you open About System, the link will point to your GitHub page.

For Base Install
sudo nano /etc/os-release
then rename id=ubuntu to id=triaxis
then sudo nano /etc/issue then change The Name Ubuntu 24.04.3 LTS To Triaxis
then sudo nano /etc/issue.net then rename Ubuntu 24.04.3 LTS To Triaxis
Then type sudo reboot Or type logout

13 Have Fun And Start Using Triaxis And You can Say I USE Triaxis BTW
